<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I just recently hit 44th level .. something that I am proud of. It took me several hours of rooting Pygmy Goblins with sharp little knives, making sure all 20 of them dont get at us ... nuking a few ... re-mezzing .. etc .... but oh well ..... there was a payoff .... me getting my level. <P><BR>These last few levels .... 43 ... and now 44 .. I have started to think more about my characters future here on DAoC. This also directly relates to ... money in Mythics pockets. Everyone wants a return on their investment. Mythic I am sure put a ton of money into this game. The coders ... the artist ... sound people ( great sound efx ) btw .... to the guys mopping the floors ... prolly an outside company or one provided by the company they lease their offices from .... still money they pay ..... but the point being, Mythic is here because of they want to provide the best online gaming exp to us ... BUT .. make money at it. Again, nothing wrong with wanting a return on an investment. <P>The otherside of the fence: <P>Me, the paying customer. <P>I think I mirror many of you out there .... the paying customer. Like the rest of you, I have the extra money and the free time ... and would like to enjoy the fun and action as well as friends that can be had on a MMORG, DAoC. But like Mythic .... the bottom line is .... I'm also wanting a return on my investment. <P>I work at the levels like ... I guess you can say putting in extra hours at the office. You do it because you would like that little bit of extra money at the end of the week. <P>I work hard for my investment to payoff .. again ... like Mythic. <P>Back to balance. ..... I'm a fair person over-all. I don't expect things to be handed to me. I hated the fact that when they finally itemized the barrows .... that the treasure dropped as easy and freely as it did. Had they made all the items a little less easier to get .... it would have added a wealth of gameplay exp to that aspect alone. Again, balance. Btw ... in the first few hours of being in the barrows, I had 2 complete sets of Delusional Power Armour .... thanks Mythic for cutting what should have been the fun experince of treasure hunting down to nothing. I also have 5 Ebony Sorcerer Staffs in the bank and have given many more away. The snowball effect here is .... people get all crap .. they give it away to newbs .... and when the newbs get to the barrows ... its not fun for them when they finally get the very cool Slender Sorcerers Ebony Staff ( iten example ). They devauled that entire experice. Again ..... balance. <P>I'm 33 years old. I'm an old school gamer. C-64, 1541 5 1/4 disk drives ... to shopping at Toys R Us, and spending 29$ for Maniac Mansion ( 1988? ). Amiga 1000 ... Amiga 500 ... 1084 Stereo monitor ... 4096 colors ( HAM ) hold an modify .. all those kick ass euro games on floppy disks. Amiga 1200 .... I've seen thousand and thousands of games. Super Nintendo ... had a Super Wild Card DX 32 ... game copier for you that don't know .. again ... 1000's of more games there .... I've been on the net since dec 93' .... had a Pee-Cee before that. Being old school amiga ... and on all the BBS's all over the world .. Germany .. Canada .. etc etc .. I've had my little hands on anything and everything ... even today .... I try out most of the games that come down the wire. <P>I am not bragging ... that was just my resume .... The point I am making is ... when it comes to gameplay / balance .. I am a fucking expert. <P>Dark Ages Of Camelot is simply put .. a great playing and looking game. The sound efx are very kick ass ... the 3d engine ... what the artist have done .... very very well done. I should know ... I'm very jaded ... I've looked at A LOT of games. This is one of the best games ever. <P>Tonight ..... at the Hib unmanned .. ours ... there was a bit of a battle. For the most part .. all I saw was ... stun .. stun ... stun .. mezz ... stun ... stun ... stun ... over and over and over and over again. I saw maybe 2 or 3 people being able to fight. The rest were rooted ... were attacked one at a time by 2 or 3 tanks at a time. Pretty (f)ucking UNBALANCED Mythic. <P>I casted a high level mezz on one tank ... and 2 healers ... guess what, they broke right the (f)uck out of them .... WHAT THE (F)UCK ? <P>Fix that (s)hit. Balance it out. <P>I want a return on my investment. This is starting to become very UN-FUN. I and many many others are becoming very annoyed .... all with very bitter tastes in our mouths ... that this crap is in the game. I dont have a problem being mezz'd .. or stunned. But to the point where none of us can even put a fight up ? WTF ? <P>I have 4 DAoC Support Autoresponse in my mailbox. I have had 4 CSR's come on and tell me that yes ... the dev team knows there are problems with then mezz / stun's ... etc. <P>Time is important here folks. .... fix this shit.... NOW. Balance this crap out. <P>On a side note. PlayNet, the Parent company to the people behind World War 2 Online filed Chapter 11. <P>Hrmm ... makes you think ... can a great thing really end up in the toilet ? <P>Answer ... it sure can.<P>--------------------<P>Wiz Bang<BR>47th Level Sorcerer<BR>Kay Server - Albion<BR>Unguilded<BR>30,000+ RP's
