Mez and Stun by themselves never killed anyone. it is the other spells that Midgaard (the least magical realm? ) have that really push this home.<P>Albion <P>..has the Wizard with 2 possible AE lines, doing up to 300 pts.<P>Hibernia<P>..Eldritch can do up to about 160 AE.<P>Now as of 12/20 the patch on Test adds a bot more damage to both the Eldritch and Wizards AE DD line. This is the lower line of the Wzard and does not take their overall capacity any higher, but does take the Eldritch up a bit. This patch also adds an AE DD spell to the mentalist.<P>But now, Midgaard...<P>.. Thane has 2 lines of AE, both are isntant and can be used while Mezzed. Total of both combined 200 Pts.<P>That that in and of itself does nto seem lik Much. It woudl seem that the Wizard should be the most horrible force on the battle field. But a Wizard can not get their AE off after a successful Mez, and a Thane can. <P>All realms have a few shouts, but a skald and thane combined is brutal. The one thing that Mez and Stun can do it pace or control a battle, but this is NOT the case against Midgaard. The problem is not what their spells can do, it is that they have so many critical spell types as instant casts. This is what hurts.<P>And putting a spell with a 24 or 29 second duraiton on a 30 second timer is a Joke. That timer needs to go to 2 minutes or so in my opinion.<P>--------------------<P>i3ullseye<BR>"You're good, but me? I'm Magic!"<P>Rictus -Sorceror(DAOC)/Rictus(EQ)<BR>DAOC Sorceror team lead...<P>Please visit our <A HREF="http://www.yesterdayland.com/popopedia/shows/toys/ty1050.php" TARGET=_blank>Sponsors!</A>  <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0">
