<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
The instacasts are the midgard edge.  And of course the healer who not only has AE stun and AE mez (a very powerful combo already) but can instacast both!<P>Can you imagine how much more powerful Sorcerers would be if we could AE stun?  Even if it was not an instacast mind you.<P>Of course there are tradeoffs. On Percival, though realm points would not show it, Albion has done extremely well against midgard.  All the paladins around gives a great advantage in ressurecting so even if we fall hard at first we nearly always end up winning the field.  It is very hard to knock Albion out because of our ressing abilities.<P>Also, though Sorcerers do not have instacast, team with a cleric!  I have a good smite cleric friend and we make a deadly duo.  Charge in with sprint and my speed spell, he instacats PB AE mez (short duration), while I proceed to long mez the rest.  His powerful smites and my spells then take them out one by one.<P>Midgard also has none of the incredibly powerful PB AE spells. These do much more damage than the ranged ones.  Last night 7 of us held a keep against 60 mids. My AE con debuff and mez kept them paralyzed by the door and our 47 wizard wiped them out in droves with his PB spell (there are some spots you can stand near the 2nd door where you cant be targeted or target anything. The PB AE needs no targeting)<P>Hibernias best tactic so far seems the pet rush.  In a large stand off they send hordes of wolves, lynxes, underhill companions to occupy your attention while long range casters and all the rangers whittle you down.  It works very well and I have been in two large Albion forces that were eventually wiped out by this. We are learning that you must quickly charge a dense pack of hibernians. They will win the drawn out long range skirmishes.<P>Lastly, what has worked very well against midgard for us is two roving groups of 8 with speed in a chatgroup. The group itself spreads out a bit and the two groups keep in contact. Our 'skirmish' formation really cuts down the effectiveness of the Healer AEs. Also, the healers stun a few of us then the others show up very soon after and kill the healers after they have used their instacasts on us. Usually this way one group of Albions takes out an equal group of Midgards.  If we don't, we have the 2nd group not far away.  Movement and staggering of assault are the way to defeat Midgard.  Don't stay too close together!<P>I quite like the RvR game the way it is and do not think Midgard is terribly overpowered.<P>Ellejienne of Percival
</FONT>
